rComments: Had him during the Summer. Very caring, honest, transparent person. He is patient with his students, and down-to-Earth kind of person, very approachable. This was very noticeable with the one-on-one sessions he had with his students. His lecture slides are very helpful. His teaching in class is good as well. One of the best profs I ever had.
He's a caring professor. Very reasonable, very approachable. I liked how he uploaded slides of the lecture before class, but I felt like the lecture could be skipped by only going over the slides.
Helpful and caring prof, really does his best to give you opportunities to do well and is always there to help out.

Just read off slides from my experience. Quickly stopped attending class so I could go through things at my own pace without constant interruptions of questions and half-given, twisted answers. Goes through individual proofs fine and replicates structure excellently but fails to truly show their underlying thought processes I found.
some of the quiz are quite hard, but reasonable. *very* good and clear class slides, you can surely rely on them. He is a nice professor, if you have any question don't bother to ask him :)
He is a nice professor who is organized and easy to understand. The pacing of the course was also manageable.

Added him because he wasn't on here. Excellent, friendly, and success-oriented professor. The course had an obscenely difficult final exam, but that appears to be due to some course restructuring problems and was curved with respect to that. Definitely the prof you want.
